Git related commands

git status
git reflog
git init
git add -A // for all files otherwise filename.
Use git add . in your bash to add all the files to the given folder.
git checkout *.cpp    <wildcard> for getting back last commited files
git commit -m message "For getting message"

To add the path before pushing
git push 'remote_name' 'branch_name'
git remote add origin https://github.com/Nizamoddin4/CPP_Programm.git

git remote rm origin // Removes the all the references.. by default name is origin.

git remote -v	

git push --set-upstream origin master


git pull 'remote_name' 'branch_name'

The git pull command is a combination of git fetch which fetches the recent commits in the local repository and git merge, which will merge the branch 
from a remote to a local branch also 'remote_name' is the repository name and 'branch_name' is the name of the specific branch.


Basic Branching and the Merging in the git.

https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Branching-Basic-Branching-and-Merging

git checkout -b iss53 // equivalent to the commands $ git branch iss53 $ git checkout iss53

